description:
Eridanus | Authentic Heavy Metal Inside

Eridanus emerged in 2005 in Porto Alegre (Brazil) as a project of guitarist Roger Feilstrecker and immediately called top producers and media attention with his powerful metal, heavy and full of feeling, reaching the figure as attracting many festivals and local TV programs. 

After 5 years of playing in the brazilian southern circuit, the group went through moments of severe reformulations and structuring, and in 2010 decided to give a new face to the band which until then had female vocals. 

In 2012 and its consolidated training with Thiago Lauer (V), Roger Feilstrecker (G), Deivid Moraes (G), Andi Castro (B) and Rafael Reis (D) Eridanus begins the process of pre-production of their debut album &quot;HellTherapy&quot; which was recorded, mixed and mastered in Caxias do Sul (Brazil) by producer Roger Fingle at Estudio Nitro. 

The official release of &quot;HellTherapy&quot; happened on August 1, 2013 and since then Eridanus has often figured on many radio stations in Norway, the Netherlands and USA, and is preparing to start the tour in dissemination of the latest release.

